Morning Martina,


I have thought this through and would prefer less posts as we are very tight on time and also don't want to inundate the audience.


Please create only three posts for next week as follows:


  1. Monday: SCI post acknowledging the week and all our services with link to video. Use a still image of the start of the video with Suzanne as the image to go with the post:


STARTS


From Bega to Ballina, Royal Rehab provides services to people with spinal cord injuries. Today marks the start of Spinal Cord Injury Awareness Week 2020. We take a look back at our celebrations last year and the role recreation plays in recovery. Find out more about our spinal injury services including our specialist spinal injury unit, the NSW Spinal Outreach Service and In-Voc, our vocational rehab service. Watch our video here < https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1XyQJcpVApo>.


ENDS


  1. Tuesday: Physiotherapy post - understand you are working with Sarah on this one.


  1. Wednesday: SCI post acknowledging the SOS Wellness Handbook - please draft a short post on this with a link to website.


We won't do a post on Multicultural Health Week.


Please load drafts onto Hootsuite and I can review in our meeting today.


Kind regards,


Trudy.
